data: {"type":"response.output_item.done","item":{"type":"fabric_dataagent_preview_call_output","id":"fco_0ad92a0e0657dd9a00699fc53a2e38819597255ebae2689d68","agent_reference":{"type":"agent_reference","name":"MyAgent","version":"413"},"response_id":"resp_0ad92a0e0657dd9a00699fc502bd408195b8abdbe6968c3590","call_id":"call_4e475b23b4a7447d85fa28a9b3373f9b","output":"{\"documents\":[{\"id\":\"f3445f72-c7de-40cb-af51-66465b8c7377\",\"content\":\"Here are some notable weather events in Texas from recent records:\\n\\n- **High Wind (Dec 30-31, 2007):** Gusts up to 71 mph measured at McDonald Observatory in the Davis Mountains. No injuries or property damage reported.\\n- **Heavy Snow (Dec 27-28, 2007):** Four inches of snow reported near Perryton and Spearman. Travel hazards, but no injuries.\\n- **Tornadoes (Dec 27, 2007):** Tornadoes observed near Slaton/Southland and north of Lubbock. No reported damage.\\n- **Winter Weather Accident (Dec 27, 2007):** Icy roads on US 287 near Canadian River Bridge caused a vehicle rollover: one fatality and three injuries.\\n- **Major Winter Pileup (Dec 22, 2007):** Whiteout from snow and wind east of Amarillo led to massive car accidents\\u2014over 150 injuries, two deaths, and more than $1.6 million in property damage.\\n\\nLet me know if you want information on other locations, event types, or time periods!\\n\",\"filepath\":\"fabric://response\",\"title\":\"Fabric Response for: weather events in Texas\",\"url\":\"https://msit.fabric.microsoft.com/groups/409e30ce-b2ad-4c80-a54d-d645227322e4/aiskills/98042b9e-11cb-422d-bd97-5873411aa7c8/stage/published/threads/thread_MuEWccMsL1Y7Q2gTKDe0QxyT/runs/run_fabVaBRXVqzitFoA3Q4PXWNuEbGm/question/msg_5r6x3T3lXBFdYFSLskZBMMJR/source/foundry\",\"metadata\":\"{\\u0022source\\u0022:\\u0022azure_fabric\\u0022,\\u0022query\\u0022:\\u0022weather events in Texas\\u0022,\\u0022data_agent_url\\u0022:\\u0022https://msit.fabric.microsoft.com/groups/409e30ce-b2ad-4c80-a54d-d645227322e4/aiskills/98042b9e-