data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_0ad92a0e0657dd9a00699fc5596bc08195b432e1dd465da9b4","logprobs":[],"output_index":2,"sequence_number":277,"text":"Notable weather events in Texas (from the available records):\n\n- **High Wind (Dec 30–31, 2007):** Gusts up to 71 mph measured at McDonald Observatory in the Davis Mountains; no injuries or property damage reported.【6:0†source】\n- **Heavy Snow (Dec 27–28, 2007):** About 4 inches of snow near Perryton and Spearman; travel hazards, no injuries reported.【6:0†source】\n- **Tornadoes (Dec 27, 2007):** Tornadoes observed near Slaton/Southland and north of Lubbock; no reported damage.【6:0†source】\n- **Winter Weather Accident (Dec 27, 2007):** Icy roads on US 287 near the Canadian River Bridge caused a rollover with **1 fatality and 3 injuries**.【6:0†source】\n- **Major Winter Pileup (Dec 22, 2007):** Whiteout conditions east of Amarillo led to massive crashes with **150+ injuries, 2 deaths, and >$1.6M property damage**.【6:0†source】\n\nIf you tell me the **time range** (e.g., last 30 days, 2023–2024) and **area** (statewide vs. specific city/county), I can narrow this down."}

